post_text: Harlem High School Math Teacher Rohini Gupta
shared_text:
Golden Apple Foundation
June 29 at 3:53 PM 路

Please join Golden Apple Foundation, in sending out a big THANK YOU and a virtual hug to our Teacher Academy Representative, Martha Kaiser, who is completing her tenure in this role at the end of the month. Don't worry! She will still be a huge part of the Golden Apple family, as she continues to volunteer as a Teacher Academy member, in her role as our leader of Teacher Mentoring and through her volunteerism in the classroom and at Golden Apple events. Whew, she does so much and we are so grateful! Rohini Gupta will continue to serve in her role as TA Rep and we will welcome a new TA Rep in July. #goldenapplefoundation #teacheracademy #teachers #volunteers #grateful #teachersmakethebestvolunteers #thankyou #virtualhug

April 2 at 2:40 PM 路

Some of NSLD's eCollections are now available to use without a library card. NSLD worked with its vendors to temporarily allow NSLD patrons with expired library cards to still have access to digital content while the library is closed. If you do not have a library card, you can also access some of the eCollections with a temporary trial account. Thank you.

post_text: Back in February, all HMS Team 7-3 students began working on a Plant Mash-up Contest. The goal was for students to create a hybrid plant that contains properties that can help our community. Attached are examples of four entries that were submitted for the chance to win a $500 Scholastic credit, $250 Scholastic Credit, or $100 Scholastic credit. One student created a hybrid of an Elderberry and Echinacea plant that "provides a natural remedy to prevent many illnesses including the common cold, flu, strep throat, sinus infections, and pneumonia." (This would be a great plant to have right now as we continue to fight the spread of the Coronavirus.) Another student mixed together a Tillandsia (air plant) and a lavender plant to create a plant that does not require soil but can be a natural remedy for stress relief and anxiety. Students will be notified by March 23rd, if they have won

post_text: Harlem giving back to our community!
shared_text:
Miss Carly's
January 29 at 8:53 PM 路

...And here is Harlem District #122 back at it again. Wow!

Harlem has gone above and beyond this year, keeping the less-fortunate in mind and teaching our youth that gratitude should be and ACTION word.

This time, they collected a mountain of warm coats, clothing, hygiene items and so much more for us! It was even organized and labeled!! That made it easier for ya to get it in the hands of the people who so desperately needed it last week. They delivered it during the first hours of a snow storm, too!

Hey, Harlem!!! We are so grateful for you and I know an awful lot of warm people who feel the same way わわわ

post_text:
The HMS Health and Physical Education classes are going to be collecting new and gently used hats and gloves for Miss Carly's in Rockford. Miss Carly's is a nonprofit Organization that helps feed and clothe homeless people in the Rockford area. Miss Carly, her family and her volunteers make and hand out lunches to over 1,400 people weekly and serve 300+ hot meals 3 days a week. Miss Carly's hands out blankets, clothing, coats, hats, gloves and many other necessities to the homeless and those in need. During the winter months the homeless are in need of hats and gloves to try to stay warm.

As a community project for our students we are going to be collecting hats and gloves. We are asking for any donations to be brought in to the HMS Physical and Health Education teachers. We will be collecting this week and next, 1/14/2020-1/24/2020. Thank you in advance for any and all help that you can provide to make this a success.

post_text: Congrats!
shared_text:
CEANCI
January 10 at 10:30 PM 路

This week 57 Harlem High School Foods students earned their Food Handlers Certifications!

Additionally, Instructor, Jacqualine Mitchel, was awarded one of the Illinois Pork Producers grants which allowed her students to work on some really neat labs! Students chose a cooking method, used spices and prepared various dishes from pork, including pizzas~ Mrs. Mitchel brought in 4 area Chefs and Managers as competition judges!

By the looks of this food I'd say we have some really talented, certified future work force ready to go!

Great job everyone and Congrats on the hard work to earn those certifications!

post_text: HMS is still raising money online to purchase a copy of Hopper for every student! Either visit Barnes and Noble and use the voucher code 12584736 between now and January 9th or visit Mrs. Shield's fundraising website: https://teacherfunder.com/harlemmiddleschool-shields/
shared_text:
Tracy Torres Shields
January 2 at 9:58 PM 路

HOOPER books for HARLEM MS

Over the past five years, HMS has hosted Mike Mullin, author of Ashfall, and Ben Mikaelsen, author of Touching Spirit Bear. Our goal is that our students will experience an author visit once while they attend HMS. This year our goal has expanded. We are working to purchase every HMS student a copy of our authors book to keep. In March, HMS will welcome Geoff Herbach, author of this years One School One Book title Hooper.

This is no small dream. Harlem Middle School has over 1,000 students. We are exploring many funding opportunities. Andys Books for Kids has graciously donated 517 books, and HMS teachers have applied for several grants. Our goal is within reach.

We have two ways you can help us. Barnes & Noble will be hosting an HMS fundraiser on January 4 online or in the store. A portion of your purchases using our voucher will be donated to our cause.

If you are unable to shop the Barnes & Noble Fundraiser, you can make a donation at https://teacherfunder.com/harlemmiddleschool-shields/

Thank you for your support.
Please share.

Miss Carly's
October 19, 2019 at 8:48 PM 路

Huge thanks to Harlem District #122 for bringing us 1,583 sack lunches the students made us!!! Holy cow this was a blessing!

They pulled up in this big, giant trailer and the people we serve jumped right into unloading the mountain of lunches!

So many people will be touched by this act of kindness. The homeless, the hungry, the human trafficked...and the youth that lovingly decorated the bags, raised the funds and packed all of this food up.

This is what community looks like.

Absolutely beautiful わ
